<TITLE> Shahbagh OC gets notice from court </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 21 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court on Thursday sent notice to officer in charge of Shahbagh police station Rezaul Karim sekking an explanation for his inefficiency and negligence in discharging duty. Dhaka Metropolitan Session Judge's Court -1 asked Rezaul to explain before court on May 25 why legal action would not be taken against him. According to the records of a mugging case filed with the police statiion on May 1, Rezaul filed the case as duty officer under criminal act 397 and 411, while he was supposed to put it under the Speedy Trial Act. The court order said mugging or mugging attempt is an act of breaching discipline. Mugger 'Raju' was caught red-handed. Not putting his case under any discipline breaching criminal act (speedy trial act) proved the inefficiency of the duty officer. bd
